How to design a bedroom for 200 kids. My wife and I love children so much that we worked hard for many years to have kids, and before we realized it, we had 200 children. Daily life became a big challenge, but luckily our house is big enough. After discussing, we decided to do this. I called a good friend who runs a business and borrowed dozens of tons of steel. We used several 200 by 200 square steel beams as the main structure, welding 60 square steel horizontally and vertically for extra strength. We poured commercial grade copper floors which will last for 100 million years. For the upper two walls, we used wood veneers to create 200 separate beds, each with its own wardrobe, for the kids to store their belongings. We bought 200 soft mattresses online to ensure comfortable beds and added soft cushions beside each bed to make sure the kids sleep well. We also installed ladders and railings to make getting in and out of bed safe and easy. Next, I drove a big truck to my second cousin's house to borrow some bookcases. We neatly placed tables and chairs on the second floor, creating study areas on both sides of the window. We brought home all kinds of books from the school library, boosting the children's knowledge reserves. Placing tables and chairs in the middle increased their learning efficiency. On the third floor, we set up a row of tables, chairs, and benches by the Window as a leisure area for the kids. Here they can gather in small groups to eat, drink and have fun when they're not studying. We placed all the fitness equipment on the first floor so the children can exercise conveniently. We installed partitions to create an independent gym. On the right, we arranged several snack racks filled with snacks the kids will love, giving them snack freedom. On the left, we set up food stalls to satisfy the children's appetites, knowing that a full stomach is key to capturing their hearts. We then installed stairs and handrails to ensure safety and convenience. In the center, we placed an oversized saint statue for the children to look up to and worship, reminding them of holiness. Finally, we installed access control to better protect the children's safety. With the house decorated like this, it easily accommodates 200 children, allowing them to enjoy a perfect, happy life.

Everybody's been clowning on this dude because he said that nobody wants a Samurai Assassin's Creed game because everyone has been begging for this for the past like decade. But to be fair, making a samurai Assassin's Creed feels like such a waste of an Assassin's Creed game. The coolest thing about the Assassin's Creed franchise is the fact that its games take us to settings that we can't experience in any other game. No other game allows you to explore Italy during its Renaissance era, America during its revolution, ancient Egypt. Even if Ubisoft was like, hey, we're making Assassins Creed Unity 2, I'd probably be more excited for that than the Japanese Assassin's Creed game. Because this is a setting we never get to explore in games. Meanwhile, why do we need another game where we learn to become a samurai when there's already ghosts of Tsushima, Neos 1 and 2, rise of Ronin? Ten years ago, a Japanese assassin Creed game sounded awesome, especially considering the fact that the franchise was still about stealth back then. Now it's like, oh cool, another setting we've seen done a thousand times already.

voice_to_text: It’s the kind of heart-stopping  wildlife encounter sailors dread. Killer whales ramming boats, at times breaking the rudders leaving the boats unsteerable or worse, sinking them. And now it's happened again. The crew of the 50-foot Alberon Coñac sailboat calling for help early Sunday, a few miles from the Strait of Gibraltar  in Moroccan waters, saying orcas damaged the rudder  and the yacht was taking on water. The crew rescued, the boat sank. The same pod of orcas have been toying with boats off the  Atlantic coast of Spain, Portugal, and France since 2020. More than 400 encounters sinking  at least five boats. This particular pod is critically endangered and scientists say returns to the same  area every year looking for bluefin tuna. Marine conservation group  Ocean Care stressing “We do not believe that the orcas’  behaviour is any form of revenge or a deliberate attack on people.” Experts think the orcas may actually be  teaching each other how to break boat rudders. Spanish Maritime Rescue now telling sailors to steer clear of the area  from April to August, stay close to the coast,  and don't try to harm the animals.

These clips are marked with text in the video. #bear #bearorman #blackbear #laketahoe #blackbears #tahoe #bearsbeingcute #wildanimalsanctuary
voice_to_text: This bear was accused of committing over 40 crimes in Lake Tahoe, but after DNA evidence cleared her name, Hank the tank is now living a well deserved happy life. In 2022. Hank the tank was connected to a string of home break ins in which she would reportedly make her way into people's kitchens and enjoy a buffet. The 500 pound black bear was labeled as extremely large by wildlife officials and a nuisance by the media. But as she started to make headlines, people all over started falling in love with her. After all, while she was causing property damage, it wasn't her fault that she was smart enough to find an easy meal. And she probably didn't even know that she was breaking any laws. However, as amusing as her crime streak may have been for third parties, the situation was becoming dangerous. Because she'd lost her fear of humans and become habituated to human food, she was determined to be a risk to public safety. As her break in count climbed, authorities said that they even started to consider the last resort option of euthanasia. But the public, including local residents, didn't want Hank the tank to be harmed and push for more investigation into the alleged crimes. As it turns out, DNA evidence showed that Hank the tank was only responsible for 21 of the break ins. Other bears were culprits for the rest. In light of this new evidence, euthanasia was taken off the Table. But Hank was still so used to human food that she wouldn't thrive being relocated to a fully wild environment. She ended up moving to a 12 acre sanctuary in Colorado called the Wild Animal Sanctuary. She's now living her best life and she even has her own pool.

video_description: Have you ever tried this? This is called a “Lemon Posset” And it only takes 3 ingredients you most likely already have! It’s sweet, creamy and has a crème brûlée style topping!  📝Ingredients 📝 ⚫️5 lemons cut in half filling removed  ⚫️1 full lemon zest  ⚫️1 full lemon juice  ⚫️2 cups heavy cream  ⚫️2/3 cup sugar  🍴Steps🍴 1)Start by mixing together your heavy cream and sugar in a medium sauce pan. heat this till a heavy simmer for 8 minutes, remove from heat and stir in lemon zest / juice.  2)Transfer the liquid into your serving dishes or halved lemons. place in fridge for 30minutes - overnight. 3)add a small amount of sugar to the top of the lemon and using a blow torch toast the sugar. And enjoy! #lemonposset #lemonsessert #dessertrecipe #easyrecipes #cremebrulee
voice_to_text: This right here is called the Lemon Pusit, and it only takes three ingredients that you probably already have. We start by grabbing our lemons, slicing them in half, and removing the flesh from the inside. Now, in a saucepan, we add some heavy cream, sugar, lemon zest, and lemon juice. And we give this a mix and let it simmer for 10 minutes. We pour the mixture into our hollowed out lemons, let it chill for four hours, and then we top them with some sugar and hit them with a blowtorch. And there you have it. This man was a menace during the Civil War. Bob Evans, also known as the Hat Man, lived in the foothills of Kentucky during the 1800s. With no wife or kids, he lived alone as a farmer to make ends meet. In the year 1864, many battles took place near his farm and many soldiers would trespass onto his property and destroy his crops while passing through. This angered Bob so much to the point that he decided to take matters into his own hands. One day, a group of soldiers LED by their captain would walk onto the property despite a large no trespassing sign, when all of a sudden a pickaxe flying through the air would strike the captain, taking his life in an instant. The group of men would quickly run back to the entrance of the property, but it was too late. The hat man was already blocking the entrance, telling the men in a sinister tone, can't y'all read the sign? It says no trespassing! The group of men would never be seen again. As the months went by, many soldiers would go missing around the area of the farm. At this point, the Hat Man had become a legend as he did not discriminate. voice_to_text: How white are Puerto Ricans? The answer may surprise you. Puerto Ricans are indeed diverse peoples with European, African and Native American ancestry. However, some people seem to think of them as if they're mulatos, yet the actual picture is much different. On average, Puerto Ricans are of 12% Tyno Amerindian descent, with Tynos being the original inhabitants of the island. Then the next largest component is sub saharan African ancestry, which is around 20% on average in Puerto Rico. Which leaves us with the final ancestral component European Puerto Ricans average 68% European ancestry, which is the largest ancestral component. Though it should be noted that the main source of European ancestry in Puerto Ricans are Spaniards from the Canary Islands, who average around 20% of North African Berberlike ancestry, as Canary Islands are located off the coast of Africa and used to be populated by Berber like guanches. As a result, the mulatto label is more applicable towards Dominicans, who we will discuss in a separate video, as Puerto Ricans are almost three quarters European.

Trash, also known as garbage how to play. The object of this two player card game is to be the first player to complete your hand of 10 cards. Pick a dealer who shuffles a standard 52 card deck of playing cards, then deals 10 cards to each player. The cards are kept face down and arranged in a 2 by 5 grid. Players do not look at these cards. The remaining cards are placed face down, forming a stock. Aces are one, twos through tens are their face value, jacks are wilds, and Queens and kings are unplayable. The non dealer goes first, then turns alternate. On your turn, draw the top card from the stock. Then if the card can be played, it is placed on its corresponding spot on the grid, with the top left being ace and continuing across each row to the bottom right, which is 10. Replace the face down card in the spot with the correct face up value, reveal the face down card and you can play that newly revealed card. If able, you continue this process until you get a duplicate rank or king or queen. Then that card is placed face up next to the stock in the discard pile and your turn ends. Moving forward, both players may now choose to either draw the top card of the stock or discard pile. If the stock runs out of cards, shuffle all but the top card of the discard into A new stock. You may replace a face up Jack with the correct card value, then move that Jack to another location. Once all the cards in a player's grid are filled, the round ends and all the cards are gathered, shuffled, and dealt again. Except this time the winner of the previous round has one less card to fill, so that they will only need ace through nine. The winner place first in this round, and the process of each winner decreasing the number of cards needed to win each round repeats until one player has one card left, the ace. Then once that player plays an ace or Jack, they win the game. Thanks for watching if you liked it!

This has been my dream ingredient for awhile now and I was finally able to source one from @Forest Meadow Ranch 💙  Emu eggs have a beautiful bluish green color with a rough texture. They are huge compared to regular chicken eggs. I was absolutely terrified when I was opening the emu egg. I used the back of a kitchen knife to gently tap the egg until it started to crack. Then I removed the top and the membrane. Today was my lucky day because the whole egg came out of the shell without breaking the yolk 🥹 I had my pan already buttered so I wouldn’t have to move the egg again. Fried eggs are my favorite so I made a fried emu egg! I like my eggs sunny side up. Once the emu egg was almost cooked the yolk has a bubble that burst and it started to leak so I had to scramble to find a plate and get it off the pan 😂 I added chives on top and then made butter fried croissant pieces to dip in the yolk. The egg whites of the emu eggs are also delicious. I made little breakfast sandwiches with the croissant pieces, the emu yolk, and some caviar! This was the perfect Saturday breakfast 💙 #emu #emueggs

And it all started when we had to take out the original windows, which exposed a lot of water damage and rotting wood. So he had to completely cut the walls and build a temporary structure to hold the roof up while he replaced the wood piece by piece. So glad we were so patient and did things the right way and took care of the major things that it could have been worse for us in the future.
